what: Development of a prior for the intrinsic growth rate
title: Life history module (lhm)
text: life history data available can populate object lhm class, obtained lhm (life-history module) package, used store manipulate life-history data. Monte-Carlo samples generated, application lhm::rCalc function class object calcuates values intrinsic growth rate rr iteration, producing object prior class. prior class contains numeric vector additional slot holding parameters associated distribution. Currently log-normal distribution supported, parameters stored object@lognormal_par.
code: library(lhm)  # initialise lhm data object for calculation of r with uncertainty rdat <- lhm(ainf = 100, iter = 200)  # then life-history vectors can be assigned to each iteration with or without uncertainty nmort(rdat) <- list(mu = 0.18) maturity(rdat) <- c(0, 0.01, 0.02, 0.06, 0.14, 0.28, 0.5, 0.72, 0.86, 0.94, 0.98, 0.99, 1) size(rdat) <- list(mu = list(Linf = 106.5, k = 0.229, t0 = 0.01)) mass(rdat) <- list(mu = list(a = 1.88e-09, b = 3.305)) sr(rdat) <- list(type = "BH", mu = 0.9, cv = 0.1)  # calculate r prior and fit log-normal distribution r <- rCalc(rdat) plot(r)

title: Life-history module
text: Module storage processing life-history data, designed allow calculation derived parameters life-history theory. Currently allows calculation intrinsic growth rate using Euler-Lotka equation. Outputs package used bdm package, implements Bayesian biomass dynamic model estimation population status using empirical catch abundance data. instance intrinsic growth rate calculated lhm used prior model fitting bdm.

title: Access or assign mass at age — mass
text: function can used access assign biomass age lhm object. Assignment can list numeric vector. list assigned provide \(\) \(b\) parameters function: $$Mass = * Length ^ b.$$ Uncertainty accross iterations lhm object can included providing either overall coefficient variation (cv) cv parameters. Overall uncertainty assumed log-normal \(\sigma = \sqrt{ln(1+cv^2)}\). Parameter uncertainty assumed normal \(\sigma = \mu * cv\). assigning numeric vector assumed replicate identical.

title: Access or assign size at age — size
text: function can used access assign size age lhm object. Assignment can list numeric vector. list assigned provide parameters von Bertalanffy growth function: $$Size = max(Linf * (1 - exp(-k*(Age-t0))),0).$$ namely Linf, k t0. Uncertainty accross iterations lhm object can included providing either overall coefficient variation (cv) cv parameters. Overall uncertainty assumed log-normal \(\sigma = \sqrt{ln(1+cv^2)}\). Parameter uncertainty assumed normal \(\sigma = \mu * cv\). assigning numeric vector assumed replicate identical.

Stock-recruitment function — sr
text: function can used access assign stock recruitment function lhm object. executing rCalc recruitment functions used calculate maximum recruits per spawner, using steepness equilibrium spawning biomass per recruit \(SBPR\). Beverton-Holt stock recruitment function recruits per spawner $$Max. Recruits Per Spawner = 4h/(SBPR * (1 - h)),$$ Ricker function $$Max. Recruits Per Spawner = h^1.25 / (SBPR * exp(ln(0.2)/0.8)).$$ introduce uncertainty steepness represented : $$h_i = 0.2 + rbeta(\alpha,\beta)(h^{MAX} - 0.2)$$ \(h^{MAX}=1\) Beverton-Holt function \(h^{MAX}\approx 165\) Ricker function. \(\alpha\) \(\beta\) parameters \(Beta\) distribution found using numerical search algorithm give mean uncertainty values approximately equal input.
